definitions.definition: ( UK , informal ) A party , celebration , social function ; usually of moderate size and formality .
examples: We’re having a bit of a do on Saturday to celebrate my birthday.
I don't like to spend time on my hairstyle, so I usually just wear a do -rag .

definitions.definition: ( chiefly fossilized ) Something that can or should be done.
examples: Don’t forget the dos and don’ts.

definitions.definition: ( chiefly obsolete , fossilized in the UK ) Something that has been done.
examples: "How come you quit?" "I'm moving to London." "Fair dos ."

definitions.definition: ( archaic ) Ado ; bustle ; stir ; to-do ; A period of confusion or argument .
( obsolete , UK , slang ) A cheat ; a swindler .
( obsolete , UK , slang ) An act of swindling ; a fraud or deception .
